---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Canary Institute | AI Safety Research & Policy">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>The Canary Institute</h1>
    <p class="tagline">AI Safety Research &amp; Public Advocacy</p>
    <p class="hero-intro">
      Independent, non-partisan research and public advocacy for the safe
      development of artificial intelligence. The people who built this technology
      are telling us it could pose a civilizational risk. We believe the public
      deserves an institution devoted to making sure that warning is heard,
      understood, and acted upon.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="section">
    <h2>The Warning</h2>
    <blockquote class="statement-block">
      <p>
        &ldquo;Mitigating the risk of extinction from AI should be a global
        priority alongside other societal-scale risks such as pandemics and
        nuclear war.&rdquo;
      </p>
      <footer>
        <strong>Statement on AI Risk</strong> &mdash; Center for AI Safety, May 2023.
        Signed by Geoffrey Hinton, Yoshua Bengio, Sam Altman, Demis Hassabis,
        Dario Amodei, and over 350 leading AI researchers, executives, and
        public figures.
      </footer>
    </blockquote>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>In Their Own Words</h2>

    <div class="quotes-grid">
      <blockquote class="quote-card">
        <p>
          &ldquo;We have no experience of what it&rsquo;s like to have things
          smarter than us. &hellip; We&rsquo;re entering a period of great
          uncertainty, where we&rsquo;re dealing with things we&rsquo;ve never
          dealt with before.&rdquo;
        </p>
        <footer>
          <strong>Geoffrey Hinton</strong> &mdash; Nobel Laureate in Physics (2024),
          often called the &ldquo;Godfather of AI.&rdquo; Resigned from Google in
          2023 to speak freely about the dangers of the technology he helped create.
        </footer>
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote class="quote-card">
        <p>
          &ldquo;It is difficult to go against your own church, but if you think
          rationally about things, there&rsquo;s no way to deny the possibility
          of catastrophic outcomes. &hellip; It was thinking about my children and
          their future that made me decide I had to act differently.&rdquo;
        </p>
        <footer>
          <strong>Yoshua Bengio</strong> &mdash; Turing Award recipient,
          most-cited living computer scientist. Chair of the International AI
          Safety Report.
        </footer>
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote class="quote-card">
        <p>
          &ldquo;There is also a longer-term existential threat that will arise
          when we create digital beings that are more intelligent than ourselves.
          We have no idea whether we can stay in control.&rdquo;
        </p>
        <footer>
          <strong>Geoffrey Hinton</strong> &mdash; Nobel Prize banquet speech,
          Stockholm, December 2024.
        </footer>
      </blockquote>

      <blockquote class="quote-card">
        <p>
          &ldquo;We don&rsquo;t have methods to make sure that these systems will
          not harm people or will not turn against people. We don&rsquo;t know how
          to do that.&rdquo;
        </p>
        <footer>
          <strong>Yoshua Bengio</strong> &mdash; CNBC interview, November 2024.
        </footer>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="section signatories-section">
    <p class="signatories-label">Among those who have publicly warned of catastrophic AI risk</p>
    <p class="signatories-names">
      Geoffrey Hinton &#xB7;
      Yoshua Bengio &#xB7;
      Stuart Russell &#xB7;
      Demis Hassabis &#xB7;
      Sam Altman &#xB7;
      Dario Amodei &#xB7;
      Bill Gates &#xB7;
      Ilya Sutskever &#xB7;
      Dawn Song &#xB7;
      Daniel Kahneman &#xB7;
      Daniel Dennett &#xB7;
      Yuval Noah Harari
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Our Mission</h2>
    <p>
      The Canary Institute is an independent, non-partisan, not-for-profit
      organization dedicated to ensuring that the development of advanced
      artificial intelligence proceeds safely and in the public interest. We
      exist because the gap between what AI researchers know and what the public
      understands has grown too wide, and the gap between what policymakers need
      and what they receive has grown too dangerous.
    </p>
    <p>
      We are not opposed to artificial intelligence. We are opposed to
      negligence. When the people building the aircraft say the wings might come
      off, it is not alarmism to call for an inspection. It is common sense.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>What We Do</h2>
    <p>
      Our work spans three domains: rigorous technical and economic analysis of
      AI capabilities and risks; public communication that makes complex safety
      arguments accessible without distortion; and policy advocacy grounded in
      evidence rather than ideology. We serve no corporate interest. We take no
      position on partisan questions. Our sole commitment is to ensuring that
      humanity retains meaningful control over the most powerful technology it has
      ever created.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .hero-intro {
    max-width: 38em;
    margin: 1.5rem auto 0;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--color-grey);
  }

  /* Statement block */
  .statement-block {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    background: #f4f4f2;
  }

  .statement-block p {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .statement-block footer {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-light-grey);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .statement-block footer strong {
    color: var(--color-dark);
  }

  /* Quote cards */
  .quotes-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .quotes-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .quote-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .quote-card p {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-dark);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .quote-card footer {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-light-grey);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .quote-card footer strong {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  /* Signatories */
  .signatories-section {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .signatories-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-light-grey);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .signatories-names {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-grey);
    line-height: 2;
  }
</style>
